text: Kinna Corpse Bride, I get the critic, but in fact a closer nod to Gutiérrez heritage and nod to one of his best episodes of the Grave Escape in El Tigre: the Adventures of Manny Rivera - in where the heroes are by chance taken to the land of the dead but with the differences be this -  In CB, Victor is still alive and not affected by the Dead Universe, as in El Tigre, Manny and Frida were alive but turning into skeletons because of their prolong exposure to the "Dead Universe" and in El Tigre like here, both worlds were are in a festive mood, in contrast with the two worlds in CB - points for keeping the two worlds Festive. Love the designs here above all the the Dead Aztec and The Charra Twin Skeletons:D. Also - the dead that ask Manolo to stay with them may likely be his deceased relatives (the Charro with two sword and Lady, are those his parents?).  In all, I'm so gonna see this one.  The one thing I can't get is why keeping body physics of the Guide, the Kids and "Ice Cube God" (that will so become a meme), different from the puppet look of the story characters?
